title: Figured it out!
message:
Figured it out!

I was looking for things that would change instead of static stuff.
Anyway, the problem was that we stored a static list of metrics in the
SnackBar undo callback. If the user added items before undoing, we would
set the wrong items and incorrectly notify the adapter. The solution is
use the latest items and insert the deleted item.

title: Massively improve UI performance across the board (#172)
message:
Massively improve UI performance across the board (#172)

- Uses a list to circumvent defensive copies of Enum native array values which are used very often
- Short circuit scout/template item updates if the user changed the item themselves
- Move tons of ViewHolder code from `bind()` to initialization
- Nuke logging code for release builds (Glide logs stuff in `bind()` which takes a few microseconds)
- Short circuit tab pager updates if it's just a name change. This is especially relevant in the "auto generate scout name" world
- Optimize the heck out of `bind()` methods and layouts

title: Fix numerous exporting bugs (#170)
message:
Fix numerous exporting bugs (#170)

- Exporting would get stuck endlessly. This was caused by the `findAvailableFile` function getting stuck in a never-ending recursive loop which the kernel eventually throttled. In addition, the notification manager used flawed synchronization which could lead to the service being killed mid-export. For safety's sake, we now have a 10 min timeout at which point we kill the service.
- File names were incorrectly generated such that `[NAME]...` -> `[NAME_(1)]...` -> `[NAME_(1)]...(1)` instead of `[NAME_(2)]...`. This was fixed by removing name generation responsibilities from
`findAvailableFile` and instead moving them to the export service which has knowledge about each file being exported.
- Fixed notifications not being updated correctly. This was cause by OS rate limiting which has been fixed by filtering published notifications to ~5/sec on the client.

title: Another massive refactor that vastly improves performance of…
message:
Another massive refactor that vastly improves performance of TeamListActivity.java by not reinitializing the adapter each time.
A benefit of doing this is that it saves on quota since we are no longer querying the database on activity rotation.
This commit also cleans up the helpers and adds fragment helpers
